<br><br>
<p>Beste docent,<br><br>Yesterday an Ans exam took place for @{items('Apply_to_each_-_send_e-mails')?['Vaktitel']} (@{items('Apply_to_each_-_send_e-mails')?['Vakcode']}). You can log in to Ans at <a href="https://ans.uva.nl">ans.uva.nl</a>.<br><br><strong>How do I start grading?</strong><br>Because Ans is a brand new application, we strongly recommend <a href="https://outlook.office365.com/book/ICTOSocialSciences@Amsuni.onmicrosoft.com/">booking an (online) an online appointment with the ICTO team</a>. During the appointment we'll walk you through the grading process and the export of the grades. Would you rather get started yourself? By navigating to your exam and clicking 'Review', you can already start grading. <a href="https://canvas.uva.nl/courses/45162/pages/tools-ans-quickstart#:~:text=When%20the%20taking,navigate%20through%20questions.">These instructions</a> further detail the grading process in Ans.<br><br><strong>Are there other graders besides you?</strong><br>Graders are added in Ans by <a href="https://support.ans.app/hc/en-us/articles/360012081058-Manage-course-users#:~:text=users%20is%20described.-,Manage,-staff%20members">adding your colleagues to your course</a> and <a href="https://support.ans.app/hc/en-us/articles/360034166593-Assign-reviewers">assigning them excercises within the exam</a>.<br><br><strong>How do I get the grades in Canvas (Final Grades)?</strong><br>Ans and the final grades menu are linked. As a result, your exam can be <a href="https://canvas.uva.nl/courses/8175/pages/final-grades-tool#:~:text=How%20to%20add%20assignments%20from%20Canvas">selected immediately in the final grades menu</a>, without any extra required steps. It's also still possible to manually <a href="https://support.ans.app/hc/en-us/articles/360036410294-Export-results">export</a> and <a href="https://canvas.uva.nl/courses/8175/pages/final-grades-tool#excel-guide1">import</a> the grades.<br><br>
<b>How do I organize an inspection?</b><br>
  After the exam, there will be a review session for students. This session, like the exam, may require technical support and laptops. In that case, contact your program coordinator to schedule the review session. ICTO will handle the rest. You can also set up a review session yourself using <a href="https://canvas.uva.nl/courses/45162/pages/tools-ans-inspection">this guide</a>, allowing you to determine how, what, and when.<br><br>
